2843efe6-396b-547e-ab48-7c2ddbf49e4c,tg:rubgr:79,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"Arthur M. Hind, An introduction to a History of Woodcut. [With a Detailed Survey of the Work Done in the Fifteenth Century, London: Constable], 1935, II, citaat p. 335: Two books printed by FRIEDRICH RIEDRER at Freiburg im Breisgau deserve mention as containing cuts now attributed to Dürer, about 1493 ([Willi] Kurth, [Albrecht] Dürer, [Sämtliche Holzschnitte, München: Holbein Verlag, 1927], 82) with a cut of the Virgin adored, by A. Bonstellen, and Riedrer's own Spiegel der wahren Rhetorik 1493 (s. 5096, H. 13914; Kurth, Dürer, 83, 84) with an excellent title-cut and an interesting rendering of the Fall of Icarus. [Vastgehecht met paperclip: krantenknipsel met afbeelding en onderschrift]: 'The first printed presentation of flight: 'The Flight of Daedalus and the Fall of Icarus', from a woodcut by Riederer, 1493, reproduced in 'The Birth of Flight', [in  handschrift]: An Anthology by Hartley Kemball Cook, [London: Allen & Unwin], 1941.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>Arthur M. Hind, An introduction to a History of Woodcut. [With a Detailed Survey of the Work Done in the Fifteenth Century, London: Constable], 1935, II, citaat p. 335: Two books printed by FRIEDRICH RIEDRER at Freiburg im Breisgau deserve mention as containing cuts now attributed to Dürer, about 1493 ([Willi] Kurth, [Albrecht] Dürer, [Sämtliche Holzschnitte, München: Holbein Verlag, 1927], 82) with a cut of the Virgin adored, by A. Bonstellen, and Riedrer's own Spiegel der wahren Rhetorik 1493 (s. 5096, H. 13914; Kurth, Dürer, 83, 84) with an excellent title-cut and an interesting rendering of the Fall of Icarus. [Vastgehecht met paperclip: krantenknipsel met afbeelding en onderschrift]: 'The first printed presentation of flight: 'The Flight of Daedalus and the Fall of Icarus', from a woodcut by Riederer, 1493, reproduced in 'The Birth of Flight', [in  handschrift]: An Anthology by Hartley Kemball Cook, [London: Allen & Unwin], 1941.</content>
